tors and von Foerster near the end of his life, this work playfully engages von Foerster in developing the difference his notion of second-order cybernetics makes for topics ranging from emergence, life, order, and thermodynamics to observation, recursion, cognition, perception, memory, and communication.The book gives an English-speaking audience a new ease of access to the rich thought and generous spirit of this remarkable and protean thinker.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aCybernetics. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 4aCinema & Media Studies. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aScience Studies. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh1 aKasenbacher, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Albert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMüller, Karl H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRooks, Elinor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311118960408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831107072980 cprintz978082325560340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823255634?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823255634423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823255634/original  a978-3-11-070729-8  Fordham University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-118960-4  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK